<p>Refresh! It dumps the <code>Genus</code> object of course, but check out the <code>subFamily</code> field!
It's not the <code>SubFamily</code> <em>ID</em> - the form field took the submitted ID, queried the
database for the <code>SubFamily</code> object and set <em>that</em> on the property. That's HUGE.</p>
<p>We're ready to save this!</p>

    
